Date Concatenations / Conditional Formatting Measures 6

Date Concatenations for Scroller

    1.  Click on Transform
    2.  Make sure WHO COVID-19 global... is selected 
    3.  Click Add Column 
    4.  Click Custom Column
    5.  Name the column "Name:"
    6.  At the right-hand side click on Name (make sure Name is highlighted)
    7.  Click "<< Insert" 
    8.  Type in Custom column formula

    Custom column formula:   

    = [Name] & ":" 

     

    Then click Home, then Close and Apply 

     

    Conditional Formatting

    1.  Add Last two measures underneath countries-aggregated by right clicking on "countries-aggregated" and then click "New measure"
    2. Type the below formulas in the bar

    .Death Color Formatting =
    SWITCH(
        TRUE(),
        [.Death WoW%] > 0 , "Red",
        [.Death WoW%] < 0 , "Green"
    )

     

    .Recovered Color Formatting =
    SWITCH(
            TRUE(),
            [.Recovered WoW%] > 0 , "Green",
        [.Recovered WoW%] < 0 , "Red"
    )
